1
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:14,820
This week, I traveled to Chicago to
deliver my final farewell address to the

2
00:00:14,821 --> 00:00:17,800
nation, following in the tradition of
presidents before me.

3
00:00:18,730 --> 00:00:20,680
It was an opportunity to say thank you.

4
00:00:21,540 --> 00:00:25,840
Whether we've seen eye-to-eye,
or rarely agreed at all, my conversations

5
00:00:25,841 --> 00:00:31,260
with you, the American people,
in living rooms and schools, at farms and

6
00:00:31,460 --> 00:00:35,740
on factory floors, at diners, and on
distant military outposts.

7
00:00:36,725 --> 00:00:39,440
All these conversations are what have kept
me honest.

8
00:00:39,441 --> 00:00:42,000
It kept me inspired, and kept me going.

9
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:44,600
Every day, I learned from you.

10
00:00:45,620 --> 00:00:48,680
You made me a better president,
and you made me a better man.

11
00:00:49,445 --> 00:00:52,880
Over the course of these eight years,
I've seen the goodness, the resilience,

12
00:00:53,710 --> 00:00:55,340
and the hope of the American people.

13
00:00:56,230 --> 00:00:58,335
I've seen neighbors looking
out for each other as we

14
00:00:58,336 --> 00:01:01,160
rescued our economy from
the worst crisis of our lifetimes.

15
00:01:02,090 --> 00:01:07,081
I've hugged cancer survivors who finally
know the security of affordable health care.

16
00:01:07,330 --> 00:01:11,940
I've seen communities like Joplin rebuild
from disaster, and cities like Boston show

17
00:01:11,941 --> 00:01:15,460
the world that no terrorist will ever
break the American spirit.

18
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:21,421
I've seen the hopeful faces of young
graduates, and our newest military officers.

19
00:01:21,810 --> 00:01:24,490
I've mourned with grieving
families searching for

20
00:01:24,491 --> 00:01:27,460
answers, and I found
grace in a Charleston church.

21
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:32,300
I've seen our scientists help a paralyzed
man regain his sense of touch,

22
00:01:33,220 --> 00:01:35,020
and our wounded warriors walk again.

23
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:40,160
I've seen our doctors and volunteers
rebuild after earthquakes, and stop

24
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:41,620
pandemics in their tracks.

25
00:01:42,850 --> 00:01:45,650
I've learned from students who are
building robots and curing diseases,

26
00:01:46,250 --> 00:01:48,980
and who will change the world in ways we
can't even imagine.

27
00:01:50,340 --> 00:01:55,180
I've seen the youngest of children remind
us of our obligations to care for our

28
00:01:55,181 --> 00:02:00,700
refugees, to work in peace, and above all,
to look out for each other.

29
00:02:01,670 --> 00:02:06,320
That's what's possible when we come
together, in the slow, hard, sometimes

30
00:02:06,321 --> 00:02:09,300
frustrating, but always vital work of
self-g government.

31
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:12,180
But we can't take our democracy for
granted.

32
00:02:13,470 --> 00:02:18,821
All of us, regardless of party, should throw
ourselves into the work of citizenship.

33
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:20,760
Not just when there's an election.

34
00:02:21,450 --> 00:02:24,315
Not just when our own
narrow interest is at

35
00:02:24,316 --> 00:02:27,821
stake, but over the
full span of a lifetime.

36
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:30,601
If you're tired of
arguing with strangers on

37
00:02:30,602 --> 00:02:33,801
the internet, try to
talk with one in real life.

38
00:02:34,310 --> 00:02:38,040
If something needs fixing, lace up your
shoes and do some organizing.

39
00:02:39,250 --> 00:02:42,280
If you're disappointed by your elected
officials, then grab a clipboard,

40
00:02:42,585 --> 00:02:45,280
get some signatures, and run for office
yourself.

41
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:51,146
Our success depends on
our participation, regardless

42
00:02:51,147 --> 00:02:54,461
of which way the
pendulum of power swings.

43
00:02:55,300 --> 00:03:00,120
It falls on each of us to be guardians of
our democracy, to embrace the joyous task

44
00:03:00,121 --> 00:03:04,360
we've been given to continually try to
improve this great nation of ours.

45
00:03:05,490 --> 00:03:11,740
Because for all our outward differences,
we all share the same proud title, Citizen.

46
00:03:13,030 --> 00:03:15,740
It has been the honor of my life to serve
you as President.

47
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:20,040
Eight years later, I am even more
optimistic about our country's promise.

48
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:24,134
And I look forward to
working along your side

49
00:03:24,135 --> 00:03:27,801
as a citizen for all
my days that remain.

50
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,560
Thanks, everybody.

51
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:30,960
God bless you.

52
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:33,040
And God bless the United States of
America.

53
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,920
God bless the United States of America.

